==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sebesten
<hw>Se*bes"ten</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧*b⟦ecr⟧s"t⟦ecr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Ar. <ets>sebest⟦amac⟧n</ets> the tree: cf. Sp.
<ets>sebesten</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The mucilaginous
drupaceous fruit of two East Indian trees (<spn>Cordia Myxa</spn>, and
<spn>Cordia latifolia</spn>), sometimes used medicinally in pectoral
diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In the West Indies the name is given to the similar
fruit of <spn>Cordia Sebestana</spn>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

